snippet.textDisplay:
Am I the only who just doesn't give a shit about expensive cars?
Like yeah you got to be rich to be able to buy one but it could be leased for all I know.
Don't get me wrong I am not hating I am a fan of the sidemen but things like the beerus chain are things that indicate wealth and being rich for me.
Things like expensive cars just seem like a flex and not a sign of being rich. A lot of german youtubers for example were flexing with all their expensive cars and so on like a year ago and nowadays they upload videos about them being broke.
I get that it is a nice and expensive car but it just has the spoiled 'rich' guy effect on me rather than damn this dude is rich.
Not hating just trying to get a different point of view please explain why you would think differently because it just seems like a pointless flex personally.
